.SS Proxy Authentication
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
To use this authentication method make sure that the
\fB{couch_httpd_auth, proxy_authentication_handler}\fP value in added to the
list of the active \fBhttpd/authentication_handlers\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
[httpd]
authentication_handlers = {couch_httpd_oauth, oauth_authentication_handler}, {couch_httpd_auth, cookie_authentication_handler}, {couch_httpd_auth, proxy_authentication_handler}, {couch_httpd_auth, default_authentication_handler}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fIProxy authentication\fP is very useful in case your application already uses
some external authentication service and you don\(aqt want to duplicate users and
their roles in CouchDB.
.sp
This authentication method allows creation of a \fIuserctx_object\fP for
remotely authenticated user. By default, the client just need to pass specific
headers to CouchDB with related request:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP \(bu 2
\fBX\-Auth\-CouchDB\-UserName\fP:
username;
.IP \(bu 2
\fBX\-Auth\-CouchDB\-Roles\fP:
list of user roles separated by a comma (\fB,\fP);
.IP \(bu 2
\fBX\-Auth\-CouchDB\-Token\fP:
authentication token. Optional, but strongly recommended to
\fBforce token be required\fP
to prevent requests from untrusted sources.
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBRequest\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
GET /_session HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5984
Accept: application/json
Content\-Type: application/json; charset=utf\-8
X\-Auth\-CouchDB\-Roles: users,blogger
X\-Auth\-CouchDB\-UserName: foo
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBResponse\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Cache\-Control: must\-revalidate
Content\-Length: 190
Content\-Type: application/json
Date: Fri, 14 Jun 2013 10:16:03 GMT
Server: CouchDB (Erlang/OTP)

{
    "info": {
        "authenticated": "proxy",
        "authentication_db": "_users",
        "authentication_handlers": [
            "oauth",
            "cookie",
            "proxy",
            "default"
        ]
    },
    "ok": true,
    "userCtx": {
        "name": "foo",
        "roles": [
            "users",
            "blogger"
        ]
    }
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Note that you don\(aqt need to request \fIsession\fP
to be authenticated by this method if all required HTTP headers are provided.
.SS OAuth Authentication
.sp
CouchDB supports OAuth 1.0 authentication (\fI\%RFC 5849\fP). OAuth provides a
method for clients to access server resources  without sharing real credentials
(username and password).
.sp
First, \fIconfigure oauth\fP, by setting consumer and token
with their secrets and binding token to real CouchDB username.
.sp
Probably, it\(aqs not good idea to work with plain curl, let use some scripting
language like Python:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
#!/usr/bin/env python2
from oauth import oauth # pip install oauth
import httplib

URL = \(aqhttp://localhost:5984/_session\(aq
CONSUMER_KEY = \(aqconsumer1\(aq
CONSUMER_SECRET = \(aqsekr1t\(aq
TOKEN = \(aqtoken1\(aq
SECRET = \(aqtokensekr1t\(aq

consumer = oauth.OAuthConsumer(CONSUMER_KEY, CONSUMER_SECRET)
token = oauth.OAuthToken(TOKEN, SECRET)
req = oauth.OAuthRequest.from_consumer_and_token(
    consumer,
    token=token,
    http_method=\(aqGET\(aq,
    http_url=URL,
    parameters={}
)
req.sign_request(oauth.OAuthSignatureMethod_HMAC_SHA1(), consumer,token)

headers = req.to_header()
headers[\(aqAccept\(aq] = \(aqapplication/json\(aq

con = httplib.HTTPConnection(\(aqlocalhost\(aq, 5984)
con.request(\(aqGET\(aq, URL, headers=headers)
resp = con.getresponse()
print resp.read()
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
or Ruby:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
#!/usr/bin/env ruby

require \(aqoauth\(aq # gem install oauth

URL = \(aqhttp://localhost:5984\(aq
CONSUMER_KEY = \(aqconsumer1\(aq
CONSUMER_SECRET = \(aqsekr1t\(aq
TOKEN = \(aqtoken1\(aq
SECRET = \(aqtokensekr1t\(aq

@consumer = OAuth::Consumer.new CONSUMER_KEY,
                                CONSUMER_SECRET,
                                {:site => URL}

@access_token = OAuth::AccessToken.new(@consumer, TOKEN, SECRET)

puts @access_token.get(\(aq/_session\(aq).body
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
