\fBThe \(ga\(ga$and\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$and\fP operator matches if all the selectors in the array match. Below is
an example using the primary index (\fB\(ga_all_docs\(ga\fP):
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "$and": [
        {
            "_id": { "$gt": null }
        },
        {
            "year": {
                "$in": [2014, 2015]
            }
        }
    ]
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBThe \(ga\(ga$or\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$or\fP operator matches if any of the selectors in the array match. Below
is an example used with an index on the field \fB"year"\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "year": 1977,
    "$or": [
        { "director": "George Lucas" },
        { "director": "Steven Spielberg" }
    ]
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBThe \(ga\(ga$not\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$not\fP operator matches if the given selector does not match. Below is an
example used with an index on the field \fB"year"\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "year": {
        "$gte": 1900
    },
    "year": {
        "$lte": 1903
    },
    "$not": {
        "year": 1901
    }
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBThe \(ga\(ga$nor\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$nor\fP operator matches if the given selector does not match. Below is an
example used with an index on the field \fB"year"\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "year": {
        "$gte": 1900
    },
    "year": {
        "$lte": 1910
    },
    "$nor": [
        { "year": 1901 },
        { "year": 1905 },
        {  "year": 1907 }
    ]
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBThe \(ga\(ga$all\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$all\fP operator matches an array value if it contains all the elements of
the argument array. Below is an example used with used with the primary index
(\fB_all_docs\fP):
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "_id": {
        "$gt": null
    },
    "genre": {
        "$all": ["Comedy","Short"]
    }
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBThe \(ga\(ga$elemMatch\(ga\(ga operator\fP
.sp
The \fB$elemMatch\fP operator matches and returns all documents that contain an
array field with at least one element matching the supplied query criteria.
Below is an example used with used with the primary index (\fB_all_docs\fP):
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.nf
.ft C
{
    "_id": { "$gt": null },
    "genre": {
        "$elemMatch": {
            "$eq": "Horror"
        }
    }
}
.ft P
.fi
.UNINDENT
